# ORIG TITLE    Russian school hostages freed by police, man arrested . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Russian police have stormed a school classroom and freed two students and a security guard who were being held hostage in the southern city of Astrakhan. Their captor, who freed a teacher earlier, had threatened to detonate what turned out to be a fake bomb and had a toy gun. His only demands were for food and drink. No-one was hurt and the man was arrested. 
